00:25:52.400 --> 00:25:54.940
be subject to the ambient
radiation of stars,

00:25:54.940 --> 00:25:57.040
and they would radiate
in the infrared.

00:25:57.040 --> 00:26:00.519
And infrared satellites have
convincingly ruled this out.

00:26:00.519 --> 00:26:02.060
If you look at what
we've done, we've

00:26:02.060 --> 00:26:05.360
ruled out dark objects all
the way from black holes down

00:26:05.360 --> 00:26:07.690
to microscopic grains of dust.

00:26:07.690 --> 00:26:11.030
All that's left is subatomic
fundamental particles,

00:26:11.030 --> 00:26:12.470
