That's tiring.

00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:16.200
So there are creatures
in this curved,

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.510
two dimensional
universe, an analog,

00:32:18.510 --> 00:32:21.490
and they will see every other
creature moving away from them.

00:32:21.490 --> 00:32:23.450
So there's a Hubble expansion.

00:32:23.450 --> 00:32:25.940
Now the key distinction
between terrestrial physics,

00:32:25.940 --> 00:32:29.340
the physics we're familiar with,
is that the Hubble expansion

00:32:29.340 --> 00:32:31.900
is a cosmological
redshift because it's

00:32:31.900 --> 00:32:33.620
the lower situation.

00:32:33.620 --> 00:32:36.770
Spacetime itself is
expanding and the galaxies

00:32:36.770 --> 00:32:39.930
are like witless, hapless
victims just being pulled apart

00:32:39.930 --> 00:32:42.020
by the expanding
fabric of space.

00:32:42.020 --> 00:32:44.960
They are not moving
through an external medium,

00:32:44.960 --> 00:32:46.200
as in the upper example.

00:32:46.200 --> 00:32:47.710
That's a Doppler shift.

00:32:47.710 --> 00:32:51.860
This is one of the fundamental
conceptual changes of the idea

00:32:51.860 --> 00:32:54.350
that Hubble introduced,
and Einstein really

00:32:54.350 --> 00:32:55.800
understood physically.

00:32:55.800 --> 00:32:58.220
We're dealing with a
situation where the universe

00:32:58.220 --> 00:32:59.940
itself is expanding.

00:32:59.940 --> 00:33:02.850
The galaxies are not
moving like shrapnel

00:33:02.850 --> 00:33:04.396
through an external medium.

00:33:04.396 --> 00:33:05.770
There is no external
medium, it's

00:33:05.770 --> 00:33:09.130
space time itself expanding.

00:33:09.130 --> 00:33:11.320
And so we have a
universe which may not

00:33:11.320 --> 00:33:13.550
have any boundary in space.

00:33:13.550 --> 00:33:15.940
And so to answer the Greek
question, all the way

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:18.310
through the ages, does
the universe have an edge?

00:33:18.310 --> 00:33:19.530
It need not.

00:33:19.530 --> 00:33:22.630
It may only have an edge in
time because of its finite age,

00:33:22.630 --> 00:33:27.110
and the distance we can see with
finite lightspeed in that age.

00:33:27.110 --> 00:33:28.850
We can't talk about
a boundary in space

00:33:28.850 --> 00:33:30.721
and we have not seen one.

00:33:30.721 --> 00:33:32.220
The other thing is
that the universe

00:33:32.220 --> 00:33:33.930
has no center, logically.

00:33:33.930 --> 00:33:36.940
And it doesn't have to be
expanding into anything.

00:33:36.940 --> 00:33:40.570
You just have to wrap
your mind around that.

00:33:40.570 --> 00:33:42.460
And then the last
weird component

00:33:42.460 --> 00:33:44.490
of the universe, which
I'll say not much about.

