00:53:51.100 --> 00:53:54.210
there is the fraction of time
when the universe was smaller

00:53:54.210 --> 00:53:55.370
than an atom.

00:53:55.370 --> 00:53:57.030
And you have to
understand that using

00:53:57.030 --> 00:53:59.910
the same physical theories
we use to understand

00:53:59.910 --> 00:54:01.640
the interior of an atom.

00:54:01.640 --> 00:54:03.830
And there are still
mysteries in that world

00:54:03.830 --> 00:54:06.850
because, as you know, there
are four forces of nature.

00:54:06.850 --> 00:54:09.520
As you go back in time
towards the Big Bang,

00:54:09.520 --> 00:54:12.140
you simulate conditions of
extraordinary temperature

00:54:12.140 --> 00:54:14.870
where these forces
become indistinguishable.

00:54:14.870 --> 00:54:16.600
They merge together.

00:54:16.600 --> 00:54:19.400
And in fact, we are looking
for a unified theory of nature

00:54:19.400 --> 00:54:22.890
that deals with the super force
that melts all of these forces

00:54:22.890 --> 00:54:23.670
together.

00:54:23.670 --> 00:54:26.200
At the moment, our
physics is only tested

00:54:26.200 --> 00:54:27.830
to the merger of
electromagnetism

00:54:27.830 --> 00:54:30.490
and weak, with hints of what
goes on before because we

00:54:30.490 --> 00:54:32.150
can't do better in the lab.

00:54:32.150 --> 00:54:34.410
In the Big Bang,
we have witnessed,

00:54:34.410 --> 00:54:37.716
or we could witness, the
super force in operation.

00:54:37.716 --> 00:54:39.340
And I'll give a taste,
again, of things

00:54:39.340 --> 00:54:41.870
that Mike should talk
about more next week,

00:54:41.870 --> 00:54:44.470
but the reason why there
are a billion photons,

00:54:44.470 --> 00:54:46.530
or several billion
photons for every particle

00:54:46.530 --> 00:54:48.880
is that a tiny imbalance
and the forces of nature

00:54:48.880 --> 00:54:51.240
early on left us
with, say, 10 billion

00:54:51.240 --> 00:54:55.000
and 1 particles for every
10 billion anti particles.

00:54:55.000 --> 00:54:58.680
And they all annihilated,
leaving a residue of matter.

00:54:58.680 --> 00:55:02.000
So the billion photons we
see cooled into microwaves

00:55:02.000 --> 00:55:03.860
represent the
totality of radiation

00:55:03.860 --> 00:55:06.350
from this matter, anti
matter annihilation.

00:55:06.350 --> 00:55:11.810
And the little residue went on
to become 100 billion galaxies.

00:55:11.810 --> 00:55:13.810
This must have been an
amazing thing to witness.

00:55:13.810 --> 00:55:14.643
Another thing that--

00:55:14.643 --> 00:55:17.100
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

