01:01:52.162 --> 01:01:54.370
There's dissipation and
decay where it sort of coasts

01:01:54.370 --> 01:01:58.020
to a halt and entropy takes
over, and matter falls apart,

01:01:58.020 --> 01:02:00.600
and you end up with a sea of
low energy photons, neutrinos,

01:02:00.600 --> 01:02:01.780
and anti neutrinos.

01:02:01.780 --> 01:02:03.880
That doesn't sound very good.

01:02:03.880 --> 01:02:06.380
There's cold death, which is
the big rip where everything

01:02:06.380 --> 01:02:08.970
dissipates and is
stretched out in a kind

01:02:08.970 --> 01:02:11.810
of dissipative cold expansion.

01:02:11.810 --> 01:02:14.260
And then, of course, there's
the possibility-- you know,

01:02:14.260 --> 01:02:16.700
there is a possibility
that it doesn't end

01:02:16.700 --> 01:02:18.120
and it would go on forever.

01:02:18.120 --> 01:02:20.940
And so you can tell
me what you prefer.

01:02:20.940 --> 01:02:22.390
