You want it to go on forever.

01:02:33.200 --> 01:02:35.490
That's very selfish of you.

01:02:35.490 --> 01:02:37.327
I mean, I don't
like to be a downer,

01:02:37.327 --> 01:02:38.660
but you're all going to be dead.

01:02:38.660 --> 01:02:40.870
It doesn't really matter.

01:02:40.870 --> 01:02:43.030
But, but, I don't
want to be a downer.

01:02:43.030 --> 01:02:45.030
I'm not going to finish
by being a downer.

01:02:45.030 --> 01:02:49.700
So here I'll just summarize
the kind of nasty scenarios,

01:02:49.700 --> 01:02:52.360
and because you want the
universe to go on forever.

01:02:52.360 --> 01:02:53.230
OK, fine.

01:02:53.230 --> 01:02:55.120
Have it your way.

01:02:55.120 --> 01:02:58.200
I will tell you the scenario
that cosmologists have come up

01:02:58.200 --> 01:03:01.160
based on these multi-dimensional
theories of space time,

01:03:01.160 --> 01:03:03.210
so cutting edge, leading edge.

01:03:03.210 --> 01:03:06.140
It may not be right, but it's
very comforting, of course.

01:03:06.140 --> 01:03:09.010
And these theories not only
have an eternal universe,

01:03:09.010 --> 01:03:11.630
but they posit that
the Big Bang was not

01:03:11.630 --> 01:03:13.620
the origination of everything.

01:03:13.620 --> 01:03:16.690
That the Big Bang was an event
in a series of events taking

01:03:16.690 --> 01:03:18.400
place in higher dimensions.

01:03:18.400 --> 01:03:20.780
So they finesse not only
the issue of ending,

01:03:20.780 --> 01:03:22.770
but the issue of
beginning itself.

01:03:22.770 --> 01:03:24.380
It's an eternal universe.

01:03:24.380 --> 01:03:26.380
And it works a
little bit like this.

01:03:26.380 --> 01:03:28.610
You have to imagine
higher dimension-- they're

01:03:28.610 --> 01:03:31.740
reduced into dimensions I can
show on a graph-- you imagine

01:03:31.740 --> 01:03:33.970
higher dimensional
membranes, or branes,

01:03:33.970 --> 01:03:37.290
as they're called in the jargon,
so these are higher dimensional

01:03:37.290 --> 01:03:39.860
spaces, maybe five
six seven dimensions

01:03:39.860 --> 01:03:42.310
within which are three
dimensions of space

01:03:42.310 --> 01:03:44.320
and one of time are embedded.

01:03:44.320 --> 01:03:46.210
And our universe, our
expanding universe

01:03:46.210 --> 01:03:49.853
is spawned by the collision
between two higher dimension

01:03:49.853 --> 01:03:51.090
branes.

01:03:51.090 --> 01:03:52.950
So the energy of
that collision is

01:03:52.950 --> 01:03:56.780
what generates the motive
force for the Big Bang.

01:03:56.780 --> 01:03:59.960
Subsequently, forces operating
in those higher dimensions

01:03:59.960 --> 01:04:01.860
pull the branes back together.

01:04:01.860 --> 01:04:04.180
The universe
expands, dissipates,

01:04:04.180 --> 01:04:05.690
but then the whole
cycle repeats.

01:04:05.690 --> 01:04:07.273
And the time scale
and in the theory's

01:04:07.273 --> 01:04:08.690
about a trillion years.

01:04:08.690 --> 01:04:11.230
So you have an eternal
universe spawning three

01:04:11.230 --> 01:04:13.240
dimensional expanding
universes filled

01:04:13.240 --> 01:04:16.940
with matter and radiation
caused by episodes that

01:04:16.940 --> 01:04:19.920
occur in higher dimensions,
and collisions of branes,

01:04:19.920 --> 01:04:21.650
or even higher
dimension things that

01:04:21.650 --> 01:04:23.160
are impossible to visualize.

01:04:23.160 --> 01:04:26.730
All of this, all of this around
us, the 100 billion galaxies,

01:04:26.730 --> 01:04:29.190
the diversity of
structure of the stars,

01:04:29.190 --> 01:04:31.420
the planets, the people
that we haven't yet met,

01:04:31.420 --> 01:04:33.460
all of this from
an iota space time.

01:04:33.460 --> 01:04:35.020
It's kind of amazing.

01:04:35.020 --> 01:04:37.830
And not to pretend that there
aren't some really profound

01:04:37.830 --> 01:04:40.380
mysteries, and you'll hear
more about those next week,

01:04:40.380 --> 01:04:43.040
but I think every now
and then you step out

01:04:43.040 --> 01:04:46.400
of your world and your life and
the things you read every day,

01:04:46.400 --> 01:04:50.180
and you feel good because
this cosmology, this idea,

01:04:50.180 --> 01:04:52.830
these ideas that are tested in
part of the edifice of science,

01:04:52.830 --> 01:04:55.720
part of what we know about
nature, and in a sense

01:04:55.720 --> 01:04:58.320
about ourselves because
we're part of this story,

01:04:58.320 --> 01:05:01.960
is one of our greatest triumphs.

